  ('Forward-Backward Quick Feet', 'forward-backward-quick-feet', 'Forward-Backward Quick Feet is a ladder-focused exercise for forward and retreating rhythm with posture preserved during direction changes.', 'BEGINNER', 7, 2, 2, 15, 30, 55, 'individual', 'Forward-Backward Quick Feet uses the ladder to build forward and retreating rhythm with posture preserved during direction changes. Best used as a crisp, low-volume skill or power exposure rather than a fatigue circuit.', 'Primary phase: Movement Intelligence. Subrole: balance_coordination_rhythm. Treat the ladder as a constraint for precision; progress speed only after clean rhythm, posture, and spacing.', 'Fast feet are only good if they are clean feet.', 'Linear ladder rhythm', 'movement_intelligence', 'balance_coordination_rhythm', 'ladder_linear_rhythm', '{"primary_joint_actions":["ankle_dorsiflexion","hip_flexion_extension","knee_drive","trunk_upright_posture"],"primary_tissues":["plantar_foot","calves","hip_flexors","glutes"],"breathing_demand":"natural rhythmic breathing","balance_demand":"dynamic balance over changing foot positions","coordination_demand":"rapid foot placement, rhythm, and spatial awareness","impact_level":1}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Forward-Backward Quick Feet uses the agility ladder as a visual target to train forward and retreating rhythm with posture preserved during direction changes. The athlete moves through the boxes with clean contacts, controlled posture, and enough rest to keep every rep crisp.","setup":["Lay the agility ladder flat and remove tripping hazards.","Show one slow walk-through rep before speed is allowed.","Start tall with eyes forward, arms ready, and feet just outside the first box."],"execution_steps":["Step through the ladder using the assigned foot pattern.","Keep contacts light, posture tall, and arms coordinated with the feet.","Finish the ladder cleanly, decelerate under control, and walk back for the next rep."],"coach_cues":["Eyes up.","Fast but 