  ('Lateral Quick Step to Stick', 'lateral-quick-step-to-stick', 'Lateral Quick Step to Stick is a ladder-focused exercise for quick lateral rhythm followed by a controlled stick and quiet landing.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, 12, 20, 45, 65, 'individual', 'Lateral Quick Step to Stick uses the ladder to build quick lateral rhythm followed by a controlled stick and quiet landing. Best used as a crisp, low-volume skill or power exposure rather than a fatigue circuit.', 'Primary phase: Resilience. Subrole: landing_braking_control. Treat the ladder as a constraint for precision; progress speed only after clean rhythm, posture, and spacing.', 'Fast feet are only good if they are clean feet.', 'Lateral brake ladder', 'resilience', 'landing_braking_control', 'ladder_landing_control', '{"primary_joint_actions":["ankle_stiffness","knee_flexion_extension","hip_absorption","landing_brake"],"primary_tissues":["plantar_foot","achilles_calf_complex","quadriceps","glutes"],"breathing_demand":"natural breathing; no breath-holding","balance_demand":"single-leg or two-foot landing control","coordination_demand":"rhythmic contacts with quiet landings","impact_level":2,"landing_control_profile":{"surface_type":"flat non-slip training surface","amplitude":"low to moderate","stick_quality":"quiet landing, knee tracks over toes, two-second control when prescribed"}}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Lateral Quick Step to Stick uses the agility ladder as a visual target to train quick lateral rhythm followed by a controlled stick and quiet landing. The athlete moves through the boxes with clean contacts, controlled posture, and enough rest to keep every rep crisp.","setup":["Place the ladder flat on a non-slip surface.","Begin just before the first box with knees soft and eyes forward.","Choose two-foot or single-leg stance exactly as prescribed."],"execution_steps":["Hop through the boxes using the pattern while keeping contacts quiet.","Land with foot, knee, and hip stacked; avoid knees diving inward.","Reset after the ladder or after each stick before the next rep."],"coach_cues":["Quiet feet.","Knees track over toes.","Stiff ankle, soft knee.","Stick means freeze."],"athlete_cues":["Land quiet.","Knees face your toes.","Freeze on the stick.","Spring off the ground, do not stomp."],"breathing_cues":["Exhale naturally on effort; avoid bracing so hard that breath stops."],"quality_gate":["Contacts stay quiet","Knee tracks well","Landing can be held for two seconds when required"],"common_faults":["Loud landings","Knee valgus","Hopping too far beyond the box","Extra steps after a stick"],"stop_signs":["Ankle, knee, or Achilles pain","Repeated knee collapse","Loud uncontrolled contacts"]}'::jsonb),
